TITLE: Black Mirror
DESCRIPTION: Originally aired in 2011 in the UK, Black Mirror made its way to Netflix in 2014. It is an unsettling, fictional series about the dark side of techology's potential. Never daring too far in the untennable science fiction direction, the show demonstrates the role of universal truth in a new age.

TITLE: Breaking Bad
DESCRIPTION: A story about a good guy doing bad things for the right reasons, Breaking Bad amassed a huge cult following over the course of five seasons. Overall, it won 16 Emmy awards along with 58 nominations, and average number of viewers increased from 1.2 million to 4.3 million during that time.

TITLE: Bruce Springstein: Born in the U.S.A.
DESCRIPTION: Initially received as a celebration of Reaganomics and embraced by the President himself, Springsteen later revealed that the album was purely intended to make Americans feel good about the country they lived in. In fact, many of the songs pointed directly to the struggle happening in America, underneath the veneer of Reaganomics.

TITLE: Call me Caitlyn
DESCRIPTION: Vanify Fair and Annie Leibowitz's coverage of Bruce Jenner's transition to his female identity Caitlyn wasn't just a story. It was a symbol. The man and the woman became an instant icon amidst the turbulent and fascinating public conversation about sexual identity.

TITLE: Dead Kennedys: In God We Trust
DESCRIPTION: The San Francisco punk band's most biting social commentary to date, this album art put a gold Christ figure on a cross of dollar bills, and placed the band at the center of punk's social protest at the time.

TITLE: E.T. Release
DESCRIPTION: Held the record for highest grossing film of all time, for 11 years (until Jurrasic Park)

TITLE: Gangham Style
DESCRIPTION: The most 'liked' video in YouTube history and the first video to reach 1 billion views. K-Pop's Gangham Style was an instant international phenomenon, attributed simply to its addictive beat and goofiness.

TITLE: Girls
DESCRIPTION: Written and directed by Lena Dunham, Girls became the new Sex and the City" for Millennials. A portrait of the millennial struggle to become your own person in the 21st century
SOURCE: the show garnered attention from the television and writing communities from Day 1. Girls is heralded and criticized for its uniquely realistic portrayal of sex

TITLE: Interstellar
DESCRIPTION: A science-fiction film about an esteemed and secret group of astronauts who find and travel through a wormhold in the universe, in an effort to find a safer place for humanity to live. A futuristic Odyssey, a hero's journey to do the right thing no matter how lonely and unsafe it is. Heavily criticized by black hold scientists, but an important film for the imagination of everyone living on this planet.

TITLE: iPad
DESCRIPTION: When Steve Job launched the iPad, he did it lounging on a sofa on stage. In doing so, he proved the need for an entirely new category between the iPhone and the laptop. This was a global statement about the new comforts of technology and the lifestyle it would soon afford us all.

TITLE: It's Halftime in America
DESCRIPTION: Chrysler's 2-minute Super Bowl commercial in 2012 told the story of the American automobile industry rebounding from the financial crisis of the late 2000s. A powerful and encouraging 'half-time pep talk' not only for the industry, but for Americans everywhere. Narrated by a Clint Eastwood and created by Weiden + Kennedy.

TITLE: Kayne: Runaway
DESCRIPTION: One year after stealing the microphone from Taylor Swift at the MTV Music Awards, Kanye released his defense in the lyrics of Runaway. Widely acclaimed as his best-written work to date, the song and 10-minute video portray a world of perfection, juxtaposed by the fact that it won't change the fact he can be a real asshole.

TITLE: Madonna: Material Girl
DESCRIPTION: Revered as the song that turned Madonna into an icon, she claimed in an interview that while material possessions last longer than emotions.

TITLE: MTV Launch
DESCRIPTION: The first music related cable station, launched in New York City. Its cheap content (music videos) initally ran 24/7, but soon the channel became a place to chart pop culture's progress. It established music video as a new tenant of the music industry, bringing fans closer to their beloved stars.

TITLE: Purple Rain
DESCRIPTION: Prince's 6th album was his most successful to that point, demonstratting a brand new inspirational crossover of R&B and funk with rock & roll.

TITLE: Run DMC My Adidas"
DESCRIPTION: This Run DMC song and subsequent Together Forever" tour photography signified a new marriage of hip hop culture and fashion. Until they sported streetwear with ostentacious accessories
SOURCE: hip hop style still rocked Afro and glam leftover looks from the late 70s."

TITLE: Samsung Selfie
DESCRIPTION: At the 2014 Oscars, Samsung worked with Oscar host Ellen Degeneres to deliver subtle, clever, real-time marketing with a group selfie of the world's most loved Holly wood stars.

TITLE: Sia
DESCRIPTION: Hyper-talented Australian pop singer continually creates global #1's yet is terrified of performing and the public eye. During a time when everyone clamors to get in front of a camera, Sia takes refuge behind physical shields -- wigs, glasses, even actors in her stead. Even during her performance on The Voice, a show about the making of pop stars.

TITLE: Target's Open House
DESCRIPTION: An unexpected and well-received brand statement, Target created a digital experience in its San Francisco City store to demonstrate a connected home in action. Rumored to excite visitors about the future as well as show its approaching feasibility. This move both elevates its partners and products, as well as positions Target as a technology-led, innovation company.

TITLE: The Arab Spring
DESCRIPTION: The Arab Spring marked the first time in history that social media played a powerful role in politics. Leveraged by peaceful protestors in Egypt, Twitter and Facebook actively amassed awareness and support of anti-government protestors. Not only did its unification powers lead to the resignation of President Mubarak, it helped turn the world's attention to the conflict and endeared supporters to the protestors.

TITLE: The Artist is Present
DESCRIPTION: Marina Abramovic, the most profound and widely known performance artist, sat in the Atrium of New York's MOMA for a total of 700 hours in silence. Any museum visitor was invited to sit across from her, also in silence. She garnered a wide and varied audience, from celebrities like Bjork and Lady Gaga, to an ex-lover, to children. The popularity of the celebrities who came to see Marina seriously expanded the artist's audience.

TITLE: The Book of Mormon
DESCRIPTION: Created by the same world-renowned cartoon satirist duo who created South Park, Matt Stone described Book of Mormon as 'an athiest's love letter to religion'. The satirical Broadway musical tells the story of two naive missionaries trying to 'save' a Ugandan community that's more concerned about their wars and famine than anything else.

TITLE: The Clash: London Calling
DESCRIPTION: America's first taste of The Clash, and the album that quickly earned them the title 'The only band that matters'. Their style introduced a new ability and perspective: To mix a diverse range of musical styles and influences.

TITLE: Thriller
DESCRIPTION: All 7 songs reached the top 10 on the Billboard Hot 100. The wide-spread success, frequent appearances on MTV, and meeting President Reagan enabled Jackson to break down racial barriers in pop music.

TITLE: Wall Street
DESCRIPTION: An Oliver Stone film that became known as a quintessential portrayal of 1980s excess. Michael Douglas won the Best Actor Oscar award, and his stock broker character famously proclaimed that greed is good.

TITLE: Zoolander 2
DESCRIPTION: The most social and surprising way to launch a film to date. To launch Zoolander 2, Ben Still and Owen Wilson crashed the Valentino runway show at Paris Fashion Week. They posted Instagram selfies with Anna Wintour and Paramount Picutres made the premier date official with a tweet. "
